nversion. The applica- tion of prescribed fire to reduce surface fuels following wildfire may reduce forest loss during subsequent fire under more extreme conditions. These findings are especially relevant given likely increases in vulnera- bility associated with climate change impacts to wildfire and forest dynamics. Key},
